namedPeople.description:
American Politician George McGovern was born George Stanley McGovern on 19th July, 1922 in Avon, South Dakota, USA and passed away on 21st Oct 2012 Sioux Falls, South Dakota, USA aged 90. He is most remembered for Runner Up For President Against Richard Nixon. His zodiac sign is Cancer.

George McGovern is a member of the following lists: Military personnel from South Dakota, American male non-fiction writers and People from Stevensville, Montana.

brands.description: A scooter or motor scooter is a motorcycle with step-through frame and a platform for the rider's feet. Elements of scooter design have been present in some of the earliest motorcycles, and motorcycles identifiable as scooters have been made from 1914 or earlier. Scooter development continued in Europe and the United States between the World Wars.

brands.description: Rite Aid is a drugstore chain in the United States and a Fortune 500 company headquartered in East Pennsboro Township, Cumberland County, Pennsylvania, near Camp Hill. Rite Aid is the largest drugstore chain on the East Coast and the third largest drugstore chain in the U.S. An offer was presented by Walgreens Boots Alliance in October 2015.
